text:
The error message "No output stream or file set for the appender named ..." in 
WriterAppender.java is misleading in the case that log is written to a 
ConsoleAppender which has no layout yet (constructor without arguments).

How to reproduce:
ConsoleAppender consoleAppender = new ConsoleAppender(/* new PatternLayout
(PatternLayout.TTCC_CONVERSION_PATTERN)*/);
Logger  logger = Logger.getLogger("com.foo");
logger.addAppender(consoleAppender);
logger.warn("...");
